cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks such as named entity recognition. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a new architecture for NER using machine learning techniques. Additionally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses Bidirectional long short-term memory networks (BiLSTM) and Transformer Encoder, which are neural network architectures. Finally, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it deals with character-level features and word-level features, which are also important in computer vision tasks.
